                        "content": "The nurse is assessing a client with a history of cardiac valve problems. Where would the nurse place the stethoscope to hear the first heart sound (S1) the loudest?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe first heart sound (S1) is heard loudest at the lower left sternal border or the apex of the heart. The apex is located at the fifth intercostal space in the left midclavicular line. Therefore, the locations in the remaining options are incorrect.\n\nClient Needs: Health Promotion and Maintenance\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Health Assessment/Physical Exam: Heart and Peripheral Vascular\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Cardiovascular: Inflammation and Structural Heart Disorders\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Assessment\nPriority Concepts: Perfusion, Clinical Judgment\nStrategies: Subject\n   Test-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the location of the loudest S1 heart sound. Think about physical assessment techniques for the cardiovascular system. Recall that S1 is heard loudest over the fifth intercostal space at the left midclavicular line.\n \n   ",
                        "id": "10786060cc18477e84f86e8eea3fb70e",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "0e9f6f70a2fe4cf4a46ee5a07f8f1783",
                                "content": "\"I will ask the client to raise the legs up to the waist and then to lower the legs slowly.\""
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "29aea2d259884065b860021aa1d4bdb1",
                                "content": "\"I will ask the client to raise the legs and to try to lower them against pressure from my hand.\""
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "99990cb7bd654514bee5cc98c509c6b7",
                                "content": "\"I will ask the client to extend the legs flat on the bed, and I will gently dorsiflex the foot forward.\""
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "9b900fa7fc6949edb82129546b058d9b",
