                        "content": "A nursing student is asked about the procedure used to elicit Homans' sign. Which response by the student indicates an understanding of this assessment technique?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHomans's sign is one indicator often used by some primary health care providers in the diagnosis of deep venous thrombosis of the leg. To elicit Homans' sign, the nurse asks the client to extend the legs flat on the bed. The nurse then grasps the foot and dorsiflexes it forward. If this causes any discomfort or resistance, the nurse would notify the primary health care provider that Homans' sign may be present. The statements in the remaining options are incorrect descriptions of this assessment technique.\n\nClient Needs: Health Promotion and Maintenance\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Evaluate Outcomes\nCognitive Ability: Evaluating\nContent Area: Health Assessment/Physical Exam: Heart and Peripheral Vascular\nIntegrated Process: Teaching and Learning\nPriority Concepts: Perfusion, Clinical Judgment\nStrategies: Subject\n   Test-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the assessment technique needed to elicit Homans' sign. Visualize this technique to assist in directing you to option 3. Also, noting the word gently in option 3 will direct you to this option.\n \n   ",
