                        "content": "The nurse would perform which action to assess for a pulse deficit?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nA pulse deficit is the difference between the apical and peripheral pulses and could indicate a dysrhythmia. If an irregularity in the pulse is noted, the nurse would check for a pulse deficit. To check for a pulse deficit the nurse would auscultate the apical heart rate and rhythm while palpating a peripheral artery and assess for a difference in the rates. A difference in the rates indicates a pulse deficit. Therefore, options 1, 2, and 4 are incorrect actions.\n\nClient Needs: Health Promotion and Maintenance\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Health Assessment/Physical Exam: Heart and Peripheral Vascular\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Assessment\nPriority Concepts: Perfusion, Health Promotion\nStrategies: Subject\n   Test-Taking Strategy:\nNote the subject, assessing for a pulse deficit. Think about the definition of a pulse deficit, and look for a relationship between the definition and an action in the options. Note that the correct option mentions measurement of both the apical pulse and a peripheral pulse.\n \n   ",
                        "id": "88c9a6065b3b473097b5f1eacec4627c",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
